## Course structure

### Arc 1: Foundations (Quests 1-5)
Installation, the three areas (working dir / staging / repo), first commit, cloning, history and diff.

### Arc 2: Branching (Quests 6-8)
Branches, merge, conflict resolution, rebase, amend, reset.

### Arc 3: Collaboration (Quests 9-13)
Remotes, pull requests, stash, cherry-pick, bisect, blame, tags.

### Arc 4: Tooling & Forges (Quests 14-19)
Hooks, aliases, GitHub/GitLab/Gitea/Forgejo, GitHub Actions, CI/CD.

### Arc 5: Beyond (Quests 20-23)
Open source contribution, GUI clients, security, Radicle (decentralized).

### Bonus Quests (A1-A6)
Git LFS, Data Science, Monorepos, Hardware, GitOps, Design.

